## Media

### Local radio and newspapers

Skagway is served by its local semimonthly paper, [The Skagway News](/The_Skagway_News), and the regional public radio station [KHNS](/KHNS). KHNS has its main studios in nearby [Haines](/Haines,_Alaska) but maintains studios and produces programs in Skagway. The Juneau-based station [KINY](/KINY) also operates a translator in town. Copies of the free regional newspaper, the [Capital City Weekly](/Capital_City_Weekly), are also available.

## Featured in media

*   Skagway and its environs during the 1897–1898 gold rush are the main setting for George Markstein's 1978 novel *Tara Kane*, which includes fictionalized versions of Soapy Smith and his gang.
*   In the [Three Stooges](/Three_Stooges) short *[In the Sweet Pie and Pie](/In_the_Sweet_Pie_and_Pie)*, Skagway gets a mention: "Edam [Neckties](/Neckties), with three convenient locations: Skagway, Alaska; [Little America](/Little_America_(exploration_base)); and [Pago Pago](/Pago_Pago)."
*   The town is a setting in the 1946 film *[Road to Utopia](/Road_to_Utopia)*, starring [Bob Hope](/Bob_Hope) and [Bing Crosby](/Bing_Crosby).
*   In Jack London's short story "The Unexpected," the characters winter in "the mushroom outfitting-town of Skaguay" before heading out to stake a claim.
*   Skagway is featured in the 1955 Western *[The Far Country](/The_Far_Country_(film))*, directed by [Anthony Mann](/Anthony_Mann).
*   It is a town in the computer game *[The Yukon Trail](/The_Yukon_Trail)*.
*   An episode of *[Homeland Security USA](/Homeland_Security_USA)* featured the Skagway border crossing, noting it as the least-used crossing in the United States.
*   The cartoon character [Dudley Do-Right](/Dudley_Do-Right) was often dispatched by Chief Inspector Fenwick to the nearby "big city" of "Skagway" to capture his nemesis, [Snidely Whiplash](/Snidely_Whiplash).
*   Skagway's [Mo Mountain Mutts](/Mo_Mountain_Mutts) gained a strange sort of fame in 2023 when a video of its "puppy bus" went viral. Even in isolation, the internet finds you.

## Health care

Skagway is served by the Dahl Memorial Clinic, the only primary health clinic in the area. It is typically staffed by three advanced nurse practitioners and three medical assistants, open on weekdays year-round, with some limited Saturday hours in the summer. [citation needed] The clinic also handles after-hours emergencies. The borough has 24/7 local EMS.

For anything serious, you're leaving. Individuals in need of dire medical attention are evacuated by helicopter or air ambulance to [Bartlett Regional Hospital](/Bartlett_Regional_Hospital) in [Juneau](/Juneau,_Alaska), a 45-minute flight away. The nearest hospital accessible by road is [Whitehorse General Hospital](/Whitehorse_General_Hospital) in [Whitehorse, Yukon](/Whitehorse,_Yukon), a two-hour drive. Plan your emergencies accordingly.